    \bullet \ar [r]\ar [d] & \bullet \ar [r]\ar [d]\ar [dr, phantom, "\lrcorner ", very near start] & \bullet \ar [d] \\
    \bullet \ar [r] & \bullet \ar [r] & \bullet 
  \end {tikzcd}


 so that the right square is a pullback. Then the left square is a
pullback if and only if the outer rectangle is.

It remains to show that the third implies the second. Let * be the
  terminal object. Given objects x and y, their product is constructed as
  the pullback





