        y\ar [r] & *\makebox [0pt][l]{;}
    \end {tikzcd}


 indeed, the respective universal properties agree. Given a parallel
  pair x\overset {f,g}{\rightrightarrows } y, we claim that their equalizer is
  constructed as the top-right of the pullback 




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
