fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Given a diagram D, the cocone functor C\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{Cocone}_F}
Set is the functor C\xrightarrow {\Delta }C^J\xrightarrow {\operatorname {Hom}(F, -)}\operatorname {Set}, where \Delta  embeds objects
as the appropriate constant functors.

The universal property of the coequalizer Y\xrightarrow {e} E of a
  diagram X\overset {f,g}{\rightrightarrows }Y is that, for any object Z equipped with
  a morphismY\xrightarrow {d} Z such that df = dg, there exists a unique
  factorization E\to  Z of d: 




